  • Constructor Details

    • Customer

      public Customer(int customerID, int divisionID, String customerName, String address, String postalCode, String phoneNum, Timestamp createDate, String createdBy, Timestamp lastUpdate, String lastUpdatedBy)
      Constructor for creating Customer objects.
      Parameters:
      customerID - Unique ID identifier per Customer.
      divisionID - Unique ID of the division (state or territory) where this customer resides.
      customerName - The Customer's name.
      address - Street and City address of the customer.
      postalCode - Customer's post code.
      phoneNum - Customer's phone Number.
      createDate - Date of customer object creation.
      createdBy - User that entered the Customers data.
      lastUpdate - Date of the last update to customer information.
      lastUpdatedBy - User that last updated the Customer data.

    • Customer

      public Customer(int divisionID, String customerName, String address, String postalCode, String phoneNum, Timestamp createDate, String createdBy, Timestamp lastUpdate, String lastUpdatedBy)
      Constructor for creating new customer objects without a Customer ID. The customer ID is set after the fact by a separate method, pulling the ID from the database.
      Parameters:
      divisionID - Unique ID of the division (state or territory) where this customer resides.
      customerName - The Customer's name.
      address - Street and City address of the customer.
      postalCode - Customer's post code.
      phoneNum - Customer's phone Number.
      createDate - Date of customer object creation.
      createdBy - User that entered the Customers data.
      lastUpdate - Date of the last update to customer information.
      lastUpdatedBy - User that last updated the Customer data.
